# Font Collection

Browse our curated collection of open-licensed fonts, designed for web developers who value **user agency**, **inspectable code**, and **minimal dependencies**.

## Our Philosophy

This font collection embodies principles of user empowerment:

- **Fork-First Architecture**: Create your own font collection by forking this repository
- **Minimal User Code**: Clean, readable CSS that you can understand and modify
- **No Lock-In**: Use fonts in any project, host anywhere, with complete independence
- **Educational Approach**: Every integration example teaches web font best practices

## Quick Start

### Via CDN (Fastest)
```css
/* Clean, semantic CSS that teaches best practices */
@font-face {
  font-family: 'Aspekta';
  src: url('https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/hund-press/font-families@v1.2.0/aspekta/fonts/webfonts/Aspekta-400.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-weight: 400;
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap; /* Prevents invisible text during font load */
}

.your-text {
  font-family: 'Aspekta', system-ui, sans-serif; /* Always provide fallbacks */
}
```

### Via ES Module (Most Flexible)
```javascript
// Import font data for programmatic use
import { aspekta } from 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/hund-press/font-families@v1.2.0/dist/modules/aspekta.js'

// Generate CSS dynamically with full font information
console.log('Available weights:', Object.keys(aspekta.weights))
```

### Fork Your Own Collection (Full Independence)
1. [Fork this repository](https://github.com/hund-press/font-families/fork) 
2. Add your own fonts to `fonts/open-fonts/`
3. Run `npm run build` to generate your catalog
4. Deploy your own font collection anywhere

